---

### Create directory structure for code
* Get copy of [BACS 350 Sample Code](https://github.com/Mark-Seaman/UNC-BACS350-2019-Fall)


### Pair Programming Game
* Count off pairs
* Start on Player 1's computer
* Repeat the full process on Player 2's computer
* Announce your score


### Step 1 - Get Mark's sample code
* Visit github account
* Download zip file
* Unpack it into Documents
* Run brackets and set directory to project 1


### Step 2 - Setup Windows for Development
* Show hidden file extensions
* Make default browser Firefox
* Create Windows Folder shortcut to Project 1
* Setup Filezilla to connect with remote server
* Copy files to remote server


### Step 3 - Test remote page
* Create browser bookmark on Bookmark bar
* Test project 1 with one-click


### Step 4 - Change the title of the page
* Use the variable to set your actual name
* Deploy and test


### Step 5 - Create an index page for Project 1
* Set a title of "BACS 350 Project 1"
* Add hyperlinks to 
    * Class website
    * Canvas
    * Your Personal Server
    * Your WordPress blog


### Step 6 - Change computers & Switch players
* Repeat steps 1-5 without making any mistakes
* Tally up your score

